						<div class="testimoniallistright">
							<p>"The potential for abuse of power through digital networks &ndash; upon which we as citizens now depend for nearly everything, including our politics &ndash; is one of the most insidious threats to democracy in the Internet age&ellipsis; This is no time for politicians and industry lobbyists in Washington to be devising new Internet censorship mechanisms, adding new opportunities for abuse of corporate and government power over online speech."</p>
